<span class="header1">COMMUNITY SERVICE</span>
<p>The occupations in this field are important. They provide services to the community.  They often use technology to provide these services. If you want to help your community and you like technology, these may be good occupations for you.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Building Inspector</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/FG/43241.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Building Inspector" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Building inspectors make sure that buildings are safe.  They work on-site, looking to see that builders follow safety codes set by the government. As a building inspector, you would make sure the building is built to stay strong. You might check, for example, that the roof could not collapse under snow. Or, you might make sure that there is an easy way to leave the building in case of a fire.  You would check the building for flaws and insist they be fixed.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>It's good to have some college courses.  You will also receive on-the-job training.  Many inspectors begin as construction workers, electricians, plumbers, or pipe fitters. They go on to become managers and then inspectors.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A building inspector can make from $27,000 to $66,000 each year.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Land Surveyor</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/FG/43169.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Land Surveyor" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you enjoy working outdoors with others, you might become a land surveyor. A land surveyor works with a team of two to four people to measure land and map out property boundaries.  Construction crews cannot start building until the land has been surveyed.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You don't need a college degree to get a job as a surveyor, but those who have a degree earn more money and get promotions. Some vocational/technical schools offer programs for land surveying.  A part-time job with a surveying company could help you to see if you would like to become a land surveyor.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary range is $25,000 to $67,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Firefighter</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/FG/1392.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Firefighter" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Firefighters control and put out fires that threaten lives or property.  As a firefighter, you would have to act quickly and responsibly in the middle of a fire or other emergency.  You would also learn CPR and first aid, so that you could help injured people. Fire fighting is dangerous and unpredictable.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You usually do not need a college degree to become a firefighter, but you must pass a written test and a test of physical strength.  Firefighters need to understand chemistry, as  certain chemical mixtures can cause a fire or explosion.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>An experienced firefighter can earn between $36,000 to $68,000.</blockquote>

