<span class="header1">TECHNOLOGY SERVICE</span>
<p>The occupations in this field combine an interest in the technical and in industry.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Industrial Labor Relations Specialist</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/FG/43222.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Industrial Labor Relations Specialist" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As an industrial labor relations specialist, you would help senior managers and employees to agree on salaries and benefits. You would need to know the labor laws.  You would also need to have wage information.  You would need to understand economic principles as well. This would help you to know what was fair for both the company and its workers.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You would need a Master's Degree for this job.  Often these specialists are lawyers who have added courses in industrial relations.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The average yearly salary is $52,000. Someone with a legal degree may earn more.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Civil Engineer</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/FG/43243.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Civil Engineer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>The word "civil" describes anything that has to do with a city. A civil engineer plans and builds structures that make our lives easier. As a civil engineer, you would plan and oversee the building of roads, bridges, and airports. You would also make sure that these structures were safe to use.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree to become a civil engineer. Many people enter into this field with a Master's Degree. Civil engineers can work in several specialty fields.  Each has its own education requirements.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>Salaries range between $40,000 to $90,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Recreation Worker</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you are outgoing and athletic, you might become a recreation worker. In this job, you would plan, organize, and direct recreational activities. You might work at playgrounds, parks, or community centers.  You might also work at theme parks, camps, and other recreational areas.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a high school diploma for this job.  Some employers look for workers who have post-high school courses in recreation.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $16,000 to $40,000. The salary will depend on the employee's education and experience.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Broadcast Technician</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/FG/1102.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Broadcast Technician" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A broadcast technician helps set up, repair, and operate the equipment used to send radio and television signals. Technicians operate cameras. They also create lighting effects and develop sound tracks. You might enjoy this job if you like working with equipment and do not mind getting your hands dirty.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need some post high school courses for this job.  Many technicians attend 2 or 3-year programs at technical institutions.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A technician can start a job at $20,000. You salary will depend on the amount of education and experience you have.</blockquote>

