<span class="header1">NATURE/WILDLIFE SERVICES</span>
<p>If you want to work outdoors and enjoy working with others, these occupations may be for you.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">City Planner</span><br /><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>City planners help cities develop areas that have become run down. Those who live within these areas have few ways of making money. As a city planner, you would work with the neighborhoods and businesses to improve these areas. You would also work to preserve parks and natural areas.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree to work in the city-planning department. A Master's Degree is required if you want to be a city planner.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $33,000 to $81,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Environmental Protection Specialist</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/FG/1285.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Environmental Protection Specialist" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>An environmental protection specialist works for the government.  In this job, you would monitor companies and manufacturers.  Your job would be to see that they obeyed the regulations which keep the air and water clean.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree in a technical field for this job.  You also need to have skills in accounting and statistics.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The starting salary of an environmental protection specialist is between $25,000 to $30,000.</blockquote>

